The article is calling on all participants of the Global COVID-19 Summit to align around global targets and take the necessary actions to end the COVID-19 pandemic and build back better. These targets and actions are drawn from various organizations and commissions, including the Multilateral Leaders Task Force on COVID-19, the Access to COVID-19 Tools (ACT)-Accelerator, the G20, the G7, and expert commissions. The targets and actions are ambitious but necessary to end the pandemic and mitigate its risks. The article emphasizes the need to work together and monitor collective progress to ensure that we stay on track. The targets include vaccinating the world, saving lives, and developing next-generation therapeutics for low-resource settings. The article calls on governments, international institutions, and the private sector to commit to these targets and take action by the fall of 2021.